The Jigawa State government has granted approval to state tertiary institutions to recruit academic and non-academic staff. The Commissioner of Education, Science and Technology, Dr. Lawan Yunusa Danzomo, made this known to newsmen in his office. According to Dr. Danzomo, this was in line with the state government’s policy in offering automatic employment to indigenous students who graduated with first-class in the state’s higher institutions in a bid to reduce unemployment among the teeming youths. Under the new arrangements, the state university, Sule Lamido University Kafin Hausa, was approved to recruit 33 staff, Jigawa Polytechnic 55 academic and non-staff, JICORAS Babura 20 staff and College of Education Gumel 60 academic and non-academic staff. Danzomo said Informatics Institute Kazaure, Jigawa State College of Education and Legal Studies Ringim and Binyaminu Polytechnic Hadejia, have forwarded their request seeking approval to recruit academic and non-academic staff. He stated that the state government has approved the absorption of staff on loan at JICORAS Babura, College of Education Gumel and Jigawa Polytechnic Dutse.